<button class="accordion">What is a chaperone in healthcare?</button>
<div class="panel">
<p>A chaperone in primary care is an adult who is present during an intimate examination of a patient. A chaperone is there to protect both the patient and the doctor or midwife from allegations of inappropriate behaviour. Their assistance is also required by the doctor or midwife during the examination.
</p> 
